    "methodology": "Processing time is measured as the average number of weeks from receipt of a complete application to dispatch of the passport, for standard adult applications. Applications volume is the total number of passport applications received in the calendar year. Fast-track availability is the percentage of summer weeks (June-September) in which the 1-week fast-track service was accepting new bookings. Backlog is the number of applications older than 10 weeks that had not been processed at the reporting date.",
